--- Section 4: Named obstruction ---
  The minimal-block-equals-bulk gap is the FAMOUS OPEN LATTICE
  PROBLEM. Closing it requires either:
    (a) structural theorem proving minimal-block = bulk on V-invariant
        subspace [no such theorem currently exists]
    (b) perturbative correction to mean-field [standard but lossy]
    (c) non-perturbative analytic derivation [the open problem]

  This stretch attempt SHARPENS the obstruction: the V-invariant
